title.narrative: 1.4 STRENGTHENED SOCIAL WORK CAPACITIESTO BETTER SUPPORT CHILDREN

description.narrative: Strengthened social work capacities to better support children with disabilities and other children in need of special protection., which contributes to Children With Disabilities, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Evaluation And Research, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid), Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Enhancing children's potential: By 2020, children of all ages have more equitable access to quality services in protection, education and health, and enhanced opportunities to realize their full potential.

description.narrative: The development of a cross-sectoral case management system (CMS) was concluded with approved tools/SOPs and an implementation plan for its nationwide rollout. A training programme on the provision of MHPSS;; services to; children, adolescents and parents was delivered to 57 social workers, counsellors and nurses.; A separate cross-sectoral training programme was designed to establish a national team of trainers on the key mandates of social workers, including psychosocial support, community outreach and case management system.; | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:13/01/2022
